<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n37009t"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n37" href="#n37009t">N37 (VI.B.28A)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n37all.htm#n37009t"> 9(t)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 364 What&apos;s a show without notoriety?</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<font size="-1">OLD AGE</font>]</font>: While Barmnum was in London, a representative of Mme. Tussaud&apos;s Wax Works called upon him to ask if he was willing to be put into immortal wax. &ldquo;Willing?&rdquo; said Barnum. &ldquo;Anxious! <mark>What&apos;s a show without notoriety!</mark>&ldquo; He was asked for his dimensions, and instead he sent his valet with samples of his socks, shoes, coat, waistcoat, trousers, frilled shirt, necktie, and hat. <small> M.R. Werner, <a name="MRWP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MRWP"><cite title="source">P.T. Barnum</cite></a> (1923) 364</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
